%N A392514 Decimal expansion of the average Euclidean distance between two randomly picked points, one of which is located in a unit cube and the other in an adjacent unit cube, both axis-parallel, with the two cubes sharing one common vertex.
%D A392514 See A392512.
%F A392514 From _Amiram Eldar_, Mar 21 2026: (Start)
%F A392514 Equals (1422 - 561*sqrt(2) - 180*sqrt(3) - 10*sqrt(5) - 81*sqrt(6) - 1344*arcsin(1/5) + 2688*arctan(1/3) + 672*log(phi) + 1260*log(2+sqrt(3)) + 735*log((1+sqrt(6))/sqrt(5)) + 84*arcsin(4/5) - 168*arcsin(sqrt(2/5)) - 693*log(1+sqrt(2)) + 21*log(2+sqrt(5)) + 168*log(sqrt(2) + sqrt(3)) - 1344*log(2) - 735*log(5)/2)/210 - Pi, where phi is the golden ratio (A001622).
%F A392514 Equals 3*(5*A073012 - A392512 - A392513). (End)
%e A392514 1.82787300624563276274725287223...
%t A392514 (* Function e[a_, b_, c_] provided in A392512 *)
%t A392514 RealDigits[15*e[1, 1, 1]/2 - 6*(2*e[1, 1, 1/2] - e[1, 1/2, 1/2]), 10, 120][[1]]
%o A392514 (PARI) my(phi = quadgen(5)); (1422 - 561*sqrt(2) - 180*sqrt(3) - 10*sqrt(5) - 81*sqrt(6) - 1344*asin(1/5) + 2688*atan(1/3) + 672*log(phi) + 1260*log(2+sqrt(3)) + 735*log((1+sqrt(6))/sqrt(5)) + 84*asin(4/5) - 168*asin(sqrt(2/5)) - 693*log(1+sqrt(2)) + 21*log(2+sqrt(5)) + 168*log(sqrt(2) + sqrt(3)) - 1344*log(2) - 735*log(5)/2)/210 - Pi \\ _Amiram Eldar_, Mar 21 2026
